Definition of OOP Concepts in Java

OOP concepts in Java are the main ideas behind Java’s Object Oriented Programming. 
They are an abstraction, encapsulation, inheritance, and polymorphism. 
Grasping them is key to understanding how Java works. 
Basically, Java OOP concepts let us create working methods and variables, 
then re-use all or part of them without compromising security.

